40 template <typename T> class handle_traits {};
41 
55 template <typename T, typename traits=handle_traits<T>> class handle {
56 private:
57  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data;
58  handle(const handle &&) = delete;
59  handle &operator=(const handle &&other) = delete;
60 protected:
64  handle(T t = 0, bool weak = false): _data(0) {
65  reset(t, weak);
66  }
67 
68  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
69  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
70 public:
71  handle(const handle &other): _data(other._data) {}
72  handle &operator=(const handle &other) {
73  _data = other._data;
74  return *this;
75  }
79  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
80  auto dummy_destructor = [](T) { return decltype(traits::destructor(0))(0); };
81  _data.reset(t, weak ? dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
82  }
83 
85  T get() const { return _data.get(); }
86 
87  bool operator==(const handle &other) const { return other._data.get() == _data.get(); }
88  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
89 };

159 struct error: public std::exception {

170 
171  error(mkldnn_status_t astatus, std::string amessage,

185 
186  static void wrap_c_api(mkldnn_status_t status,
187  std::string message,
188  mkldnn_primitive_t *error_primitive = 0)
189  {
190  if (status != mkldnn_success) {
191  if (nullptr != error_primitive)
192  throw error(status, message, *error_primitive);
193  else
194  throw error(status, message, nullptr);
195  }
196  }
197 };

431  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const
432  {
433  int count, c_mask;
434  const float *c_scales;
435  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(get(),
436  &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
437  "could not get int output scales");
438  scales.resize(count);
439 
440  mask = c_mask;
441  for (int c = 0; c < count; ++c)
442  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
443  }
444 
445  void set_output_scales(int mask, const std::vector<float> &scales)
446  {
447  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_attr_set_output_scales(get(),
448  (int)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
449  "could not set int output scales");
450  }

720  memory(const primitive &aprimitive): primitive(aprimitive) {}
724  memory(const primitive_desc &adesc) {
725  mkldnn_primitive_t result;
726  error::wrap_c_api(
727  mkldnn_primitive_create(&result, adesc.get(), nullptr, nullptr),
728  "could not create a memory primitive");
729  reset(result);
730  auto _malloc = [](size_t size, int alignment) {
731  void *ptr;
732 #ifdef _WIN32
733  ptr = _aligned_malloc(size, alignment);
734  int rc = ((ptr)? 0 : errno);
735 #else
736  int rc = ::posix_memalign(&ptr, alignment, size);
737 #endif /* _WIN32 */
738  return (rc == 0) ? (char*)ptr : nullptr;
739  };
740  auto _free = [](char* p) {
741 #ifdef _WIN32
742  _aligned_free((void*)p);
743 #else
744  ::free((void*)p);
745 #endif /* _WIN32 */
746  };
747  _handle.reset(_malloc(adesc.get_size(), 4096), _free);
748  set_data_handle(_handle.get());
749  }

755  "could not create a memory primitive");
756  reset(result);

2755  batch_normalization_forward(const primitive_desc &aprimitive_desc,
2756  const primitive::at &src, const memory &dst, const memory &mean,
2757  const memory &variance, const memory &workspace) {
2758  mkldnn_primitive_t result;
2759  mkldnn_primitive_at_t inputs[2] = { src.data };
2760  const_mkldnn_primitive_t outputs[4] = { dst.get(),
2761  mean.get(), variance.get(), workspace.get() };
2762 
2763  if (1) { // check whether this is the `wrong` constructor
2764  const int n_inputs_expected = mkldnn_primitive_desc_query_s32(
2765  aprimitive_desc.get(), mkldnn_query_num_of_inputs_s32, 0);
2766  const int n_outputs_expected = mkldnn_primitive_desc_query_s32(
2767  aprimitive_desc.get(), mkldnn_query_num_of_outputs_s32, 0);
2768  if (n_inputs_expected == 2 && n_outputs_expected == 3) {
2769  // shift parameters, get rid of workspace, and add weights...
2770  auto _weights = dst;
2771  inputs[1] = {_weights.get(), 0};
2772 
2773  auto _dst = mean, _mean = variance, _variance = workspace;
2774  outputs[0] = _dst.get();
2775  outputs[1] = _mean.get();
2776  outputs[2] = _variance.get();
2777  outputs[3] = nullptr;
2778  }
2779  }
2780  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_create(&result,
2781  aprimitive_desc.get(), inputs, outputs),
2782  "could not create a batch normalization forward primitive");
2783  reset(result);
2784  }
